Description: MSCI World Index: Measures the performance of large and mid-cap stocks across 23 Developed Markets (DM) countries.
Nikkei 225 Stock Average (Japan): A price-weighted stock index of 225 large companies on the Tokyo Stock Exchange.
STOXX Europe 600 Total Market Index (Total Return): Broad pan-European index covering large, mid, and small market capitalisation companies.
S&P 500 Total Return Index: A market-cap weighted index of 500 leading US publicly traded companies, including reinvested dividends.
Gold Futures (Generic 1st contract): The ticker for the front-month Gold futures contract on exchanges like COMEX/NYMEX.
WTI Crude Oil Futures (Generic 1st contract): The ticker for the front-month West Texas Intermediate (WTI) crude oil futures contract on NYMEX.
3-Month EURIBOR: The benchmark interest rate indicating the average rate at which major banks in the Eurozone lend unsecured funds to one another.
Effective Federal Funds Rate (EFFR) / US Treasury Rate 3M: Represents the effective target rate for overnight US interbank borrowing (or related short-term US Treasury rates).
US Treasury Yield Spread (10-Year minus 2-Year): The difference between the 10-year and 2-year US Treasury Constant Maturity yields.
Merrill Lynch Option Volatility Estimate (MOVE) Index: A measure of implied volatility of the US Treasury market (bond market).
Cboe Volatility Index: The premier measure of the stock marketâ€™s expectation of 30-day volatility based on S&P 500 (SPX) index options.
VSTOXX Index: A measure of expected volatility in the European stock market, based on EURO STOXX 50 index options.
Nikkei Volatility Index (Implied Volatility Nikkei): A measure of expected volatility in the Japanese stock market, based on Nikkei 225 options.
S&P 500 Price Index: The primary market-cap weighted index of 500 leading US publicly traded companies (excludes dividends).
